The paper proposes a system for graph mining tasks, which involves processing large graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on distributed processing and efficient execution also supports the likelihood of cs.DC and cs.SI.
